 Reports of child sex abuse cases have risen by more than 60 per cent in the wake of Operation Yewtree and the Rotherham scandal .
Figures revealed thousands more people had contacted police with allegations of abuse since 2011 , with nearly 9,000 reports filed in 2014 .
Despite a surge in reports , the number of arrests fell by nine per cent , the figures .
